Ubuntu 12.04 LTS
OpenSSH
http://www.leonardteo.com/p/install-ruby-on-rails-on-ubuntu-server
Modified the script to use lastest release of Ruby (http://ftp.ruby-lang.org/pub/ruby/1.9/ruby-1.9.3-p392.tar.gz)
    sudo apt-get install -y git && git clone https://github.com/ballistiq/ruby-passenger-nginx-installer.git
    sudo bash ./ruby-passenger-nginx-installer/install.sh

Install MySQL
    sudo apt-get install -y mysql-server
Create databases
    create database soccer_production
    create database soccer_staging

Create Folders
    sudo mkdir /webapps
    sudo chown <user>:<user> /webapps
    mkdir /webapps/centralmarinsoccer
    mkdir /webapps/centralmarinsoccer-staging

    ln -s /webapps/centralmarinsoccer ~/production
    ln -s /webapps/centralmarinsoccer-staging ~/staging

Create SSH keys and add them to repo
    ssh-keygen -t rsa
Add public key to repo

Add Hosts entry for repo pointing to 192.168.1.16
Update known hosts to add repo by doing an ssh to the box

Deployment Machine
    cap deploy:setup
    cap deploy

    cap production deploy:setup
    cap production deploy